Boston College  reached the
semifinals of the National Collegiate Athletic Association menâ€™s
hockey tournament with its 17th straight victory, 4-0 over
defending champion Minnesota-Duluth.  Johnny Gaudreau and Patrick Wey each had a goal and an
assist for top-ranked Boston College (31-10-1) yesterday in
Worcester,  Massachusetts , while goaltender Parker Milner had 33
saves. The Eagles advance to play the University of  Minnesota  in
the  Frozen Four  on April 5 in Tampa,  Florida .  Minnesota (28-13-1) beat North Dakota 5-2 yesterday to win
the West Regional in  St. Paul , Minnesota.  Ferris State and Union College of New York will meet in the
other national semifinal in Tampa on April 5. The championship
game will be played two days later.  To contact the reporter on this story:
